element.name: Contract
element.documentation:
A contract contains the agreements that the data controller and data processor have made concerning subject matter and duration of the processing, the nature and purpose of the processing, the type of personal data to be processed, the categories of data subjects and the obligations and rights of the controller.
Agreements made between data controller and data processor should be reflected in the data processing agreements of both parties.

element.name: Data processing agreement
element.documentation: Data controllers (resources) are obliged to enter into a written contract with each data processor (clients) The data processing agreement sets out the subject matter and duration of the processing, the nature and purpose of the processing, the type of personal data to be processed, the categories of data subjects and the obligations and rights of the controller.

element.name: NLX API directory
element.documentation: The API directory lists all APIs offered on the NLX network by NLX inways.

element.name: Client application log
element.documentation: Process-id: Unique identifier of originating process Log record-id: Unique identifier of API-request Application-id: Application which made the call User-id: End-user identification Why: Purpose specification (from matrix) What: Name of NLX-outway called When: Timestamp Data-request: Requested data elements/categories Data-response: Received data elements/categories Result code: Code representing if the call was a success Result description: Description of error if call not successful

element.name: NLX outway log
element.documentation: Organisation-id: Organisation which made the call (the API consumer) Log record-id: Unique identifier of API-request (provided by API consumer) Why: Purpose specification (provided by API consumer) What: Name of API connected to NLX-inway When: Timestamp Result code: Code representing if the call was a success Result description: Description of error if call not successful

element.name: NLX inway log
element.documentation: Organisation-id: Organisation which made the call (the API consumer) Log record-id: Unique identifier of API-request (provided by API consumer) Why: Purpose specification (provided by API consumer) What: Name of API connected to NLX-inway When: Timestamp Result code: Code representing if the call was a success Result description: Description of error if call not successful

element.name: Secure network communication
element.documentation: Communication between NLX clients and resources is based on mutual TLS. In a testing and demo environment the NLX provides a certificate authority.

element.name: NLX node (client)
element.documentation: The NLX node hosted by the client logs all calls to NLX inway and outway interfaces.

element.name: Outway
element.documentation: An outway interface is used by client applications to call APIs offered by inway interfaces of NLX nodes.

element.name: Resource application log
element.documentation: Organisation-id: Organisation which made the call (the API consumer) Log record-id: Unique identifier of API-request (provided by API consumer) Why: Purpose specification (provided by API consumer) What: API name When: Timestamp Data-request: Requested data elements/categories Data-response: Received data elements/categories Result code: Code representing if the call was a success Result description: Description of error if call not successful

element.name: NLX node (resource)
element.documentation: The NLX node hosted by the resource logs all calls to NLX inway and outway interfaces.

element.name: Inway
element.documentation:
Inways are used to publish APIs on the NLX network. Inways connects itself to the NLX network and registers its services on the NLX network.
Inways check if the organisation making the request has sufficient access rights by checking the data processing agreement that has been drafted between the resource and client organisations.

relationship.documentation: The inway interface routes the call to the connected inway interface of the requesting NLX outway.
The NLX outway interface returns the result of the call to the NLX inway to the client application.

relationship.name: Mutual TLS or API-key
relationship.documentation: Client applications communicate with the NLX outway through eiter mutual TLS (self-signed certificates) or API-keys.
Client application calls an outway interface of an NLX node. The client application provides metadata for the call in the header and provides the call payload.
End-user can only access application functions for which he/she is authorised. Access rights for end-users are managed in a directory service.
The inway interface routes calls from an NLX outway to a resource application API.

The outway interface logs the call in the NLX log and routes the call to the connected inway interface of an NLX node resource. The NLX node resource can be hosted by an external organisation or by the local organisation .
The API returns the requested data to the NLX inway interface. The API returns metadata such as return codes indicating if the call was succesful.

view.name: Authentication and authorisation
view.documentation: Authentication on basis of mutual TLS. Certificates are provided by a central certicate authority.
